give(uint256,address).details: ImportCdpProxy will freely give away any cdps it owns

importCdp(address,uint256,uint256).details: Migrate a CDPMgr-controlled MakerDAO vault to Yield. This function can be called from a dsproxy that already has a `vat.hope` on the user's MakerDAO Vault

params.maxDaiPrice: Maximum fyDai price to pay for Dai
params.pool: fyDai Pool to use for migration, determining maturity of the Yield Vault

importCdpFromProxy(address,address,uint2.details: Transfer debt and collateral from MakerDAO (this contract's CDP) to Yield (user's CDP) Needs controller.addDelegate(importCdpProxy.address, { from: user });

params.cdp: The The CDP id containing the debt and collateral to migrate
params.debtAmount: Normalized dai debt to move from MakerDAO to Yield. ndai * rate = dai
params.maxDaiPrice: Maximum fyDai price to pay for Dai
params.pool: The pool to trade in (and therefore fyDai series to borrow)
params.user: The user to receive the debt and collateral in Yield
params.wethAmount: weth to move from MakerDAO to Yield. Needs to be high enough to collateralize the dai debt in Yield, and low enough to make sure that debt left in MakerDAO is also collateralized.

params.debtAmount: Normalized debt to move ndai * rate = dai
params.maxDaiPrice: Maximum fyDai price to pay for Dai

importCdpPositionCheck(uint256).details: Determine whether all approvals and signatures are in place for `importCdpPosition`.

params.cdp: MakerDAO CDP to import. If `return[0]` is `false`, calling `cdpMgr.cdpAllow(cdp, proxy.address, 1)` will set the MakerDAO approval. If `return[1]` is `false`, `importCdpFromProxyWithSignature` must be called with a controller signature. If `return` is `(true, true)`, `importCdpFromProxy` won't fail because of missing approvals or signatures.

importCdpPositionWithSignature(address,u.details: Transfer debt and collateral from MakerDAO to Yield Needs `cdpMgr.cdpAllow(cdp, proxy.address, 1)`

params.cdp: The CDP containing the migrated debt and collateral, its owner will own the Yield vault.
params.controllerSig: packed signature for delegation of ImportCdpProxy (not dsproxy) in the controller. Ignored if '0x'.
params.debtAmount: dai debt to move from MakerDAO to Yield. Denominated in Dai (= art * rate)
params.maxDaiPrice: Maximum fyDai price to pay for Dai
params.pool: The pool to trade in (and therefore fyDai series to borrow)
params.wethAmount: weth to move from MakerDAO to Yield. Needs to be high enough to collateralize the dai debt in Yield, and low enough to make sure that debt left in MakerDAO is also collateralized.

importCdpWithSignature(address,uint256,u.details: Transfer a CDP from MakerDAO to Yield Needs `cdpMgr.cdpAllow(cdp, proxy.address, 1)`

params.cdp: The CDP containing the migrated debt and collateral, its owner will own the Yield vault.
params.controllerSig: packed signature for delegation of ImportCdpProxy (not dsproxy) in the controller. Ignored if '0x'.
params.maxDaiPrice: Maximum fyDai price to pay for Dai
params.pool: The pool to trade in (and therefore fyDai series to borrow)
